1-6 Riverview Terrace, at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of East 58th Street, as seen from the Queensboro Bridge. Also shown is the south side of East 58th Street, from the East River to Sutton Place (York Avenue). A United States Life Saving Corps Building is shown at the foot of 58th Street.

P. L. Sperr

(2)

The above enumerated buildings solely, as photographed from the ground level. No. 6, the residence at the right, is to be redesigned according to the New York Times of August 9, 1939. Ely Jacques Kahn and Robert Allan Jacobs are the architects for the owner Marco F. Hellman.

George D. Chinn
title: Manhattan: Riverview Terrace - 58th Street (East)
